{"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Path\/foregroundStyle(_:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"sections":[],"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"OpenSwiftUI","relatedModules":["OpenSwiftUICore"]}],"title":"foregroundStyle(_:)","platforms":[{"beta":false,"unavailable":false,"introducedAt":"13.0","name":"iOS","deprecated":false},{"beta":false,"unavailable":false,"introducedAt":"10.15","name":"macOS","deprecated":false},{"beta":false,"unavailable":false,"introducedAt":"13.0","name":"tvOS","deprecated":false},{"beta":false,"unavailable":false,"introducedAt":"1.0","name":"visionOS","deprecated":false},{"beta":false,"unavailable":false,"introducedAt":"6.0","name":"watchOS","deprecated":false}],"externalID":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewPAAE15foregroundStyleyQrqd__AA05ShapeF0Rd__lF::SYNTHESIZED::s:15OpenSwiftUICore4PathV","symbolKind":"method","roleHeading":"Instance Method","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"foregroundStyle"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"kind":"genericParameter","text":"S"},{"kind":"text","text":">("},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"S"},{"kind":"text","text":") -> "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"some"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP","text":"View"}],"remoteSource":{"url":"https:\/\/github.com\/OpenSwiftUIProject\/OpenSwiftUI\/blob\/main\/Sources\/OpenSwiftUICore\/Shape\/ShapeStyle\/ForegroundStyleModifier.swift#L112","fileName":"ForegroundStyleModifier.swift"},"extendedModule":"OpenSwiftUICore","role":"symbol"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Sets a view’s foreground elements to use a given style."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"attribute","text":"nonisolated"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"foregroundStyle"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"kind":"genericParameter","text":"S"},{"kind":"text","text":">("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"_"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"internalParam","text":"style"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"S"},{"kind":"text","text":") -> "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"some"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"View","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"where"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"S"},{"kind":"text","text":" : "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"ShapeStyle","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ShapeStyle","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore10ShapeStyleP"},{"kind":"text","text":"\n"}],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"parameters","parameters":[{"name":"style","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The color or pattern to use when filling in the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"foreground elements. To indicate a specific value, use ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Color","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" or","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"ShapeStyle\/image(_:sourceRect:scale:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", or one of the gradient","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"types, like","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"ShapeStyle\/linearGradient(colors:startPoint:endPoint:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". To set a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"style that’s relative to the containing view’s style, use one of the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"semantic styles, like ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ShapeStyle\/primary","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Return Value","anchor":"return-value","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A view that uses the given foreground style.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Use this method to style","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"foreground content like text, shapes, and template images","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(including symbols):","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["HStack {","    Image(systemName: \"triangle.fill\")","    Text(\"Hello, world!\")","    RoundedRectangle(cornerRadius: 5)","        .frame(width: 40, height: 20)","}",".foregroundStyle(.teal)"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The example above creates a row of ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ShapeStyle\/teal","type":"reference"},{"text":" foreground","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"elements:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can use any style that conforms to the "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ShapeStyle"},{"type":"text","text":" protocol,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"like the "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ShapeStyle\/teal"},{"type":"text","text":" color in the example above, or the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ShapeStyle\/linearGradient(colors:startPoint:endPoint:)"},{"type":"text","text":" gradient"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"shown below:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["Text(\"Gradient Text\")","    .font(.largeTitle)","    .foregroundStyle(","        .linearGradient(","            colors: [.yellow, .blue],","            startPoint: .top,","            endPoint: .bottom","        )","    )"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[]},{"name":"Tip","style":"tip","type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If you want to fill a single ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Shape"},{"text":" instance with a style,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"use the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Shape\/fill(style:)"},{"text":" shape modifier instead because it’s more","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"efficient.","type":"text"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"OpenSwiftUI creates a context-dependent render for a given style.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"For example, a ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Color"},{"text":" that you load from an asset catalog","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"can have different light and dark appearances, while some styles","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"also vary by platform.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Hierarchical foreground styles like "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ShapeStyle\/secondary"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"don’t impose a style of their own, but instead modify other styles."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"In particular, they modify the primary"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"level of the current foreground style to the degree given by"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the hierarchical style’s name."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"To find the current foreground style to modify, OpenSwiftUI looks for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the innermost containing style that you apply with the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"foregroundStyle(_:)"},{"type":"text","text":" or the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View\/foregroundColor(_:)","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" modifier."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"If you haven’t specified a style, OpenSwiftUI uses the default foreground"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"style, as in the following example:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["VStack(alignment: .leading) {","    Label(\"Primary\", systemImage: \"1.square.fill\")","    Label(\"Secondary\", systemImage: \"2.square.fill\")","        .foregroundStyle(.secondary)","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you add a foreground style on the enclosing"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/VStack","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":", the hierarchical styling responds accordingly:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["VStack(alignment: .leading) {","    Label(\"Primary\", systemImage: \"1.square.fill\")","    Label(\"Secondary\", systemImage: \"2.square.fill\")","        .foregroundStyle(.secondary)","}",".foregroundStyle(.blue)"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"When you apply a custom style to a view, the view disables the vibrancy","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"effect for foreground elements in that view, or in any of its child","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"views, that it would otherwise gain from adding a background material","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"— for example, using the ","type":"text"},{"code":"View\/background(_:ignoresSafeAreaEdges:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"modifier. However, hierarchical styles applied to the default foreground","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"don’t disable vibrancy.","type":"text"}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI","doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Path"]]},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/openswiftui\/path\/foregroundstyle(_:)"]}],"references":{"doc://OpenSwiftUI/documentation/OpenSwiftUI/ShapeStyle":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A color or pattern to use when rendering a shape."}],"type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"ShapeStyle","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","title":"ShapeStyle","kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"ShapeStyle","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ShapeStyle","url":"\/documentation\/openswiftui\/shapestyle"},"doc://OpenSwiftUI/documentation/OpenSwiftUI/View":{"fragments":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"View","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"View","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"View","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A type that represents part of your app’s user interface and provides"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"modifiers that you use to configure views."}],"url":"\/documentation\/openswiftui\/view","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View","role":"symbol"},"doc://OpenSwiftUI/documentation/OpenSwiftUI/ShapeStyle/teal":{"kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/openswiftui\/shapestyle\/teal","type":"topic","title":"teal","abstract":[{"text":"A context-dependent teal color suitable for use in UI elements.","typ